# Feature Updates on Homepage

When you complete a significant feature or ship a major update, add it to the recent updates shown on the homepage.

## How

Edit `lib/updates.ts` and add a new entry to the `FEATURE_UPDATES` array:

```typescript
{
  date: "YYYY-MM",  // e.g. "2026-02"
  title: "Feature name",
  description: "One-line description of what users get.",
},
```

Add new entries at the **top** of the array so the most recent updates appear first.

## When

- New user-facing features (e.g. marketplace, gallery, new page)
- Major improvements to existing features
- Not: minor bug fixes, refactors, or internal changes
